                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">How about this. If you're dead set on yourself being an enchanter and you want a healer along with another class your for your friend. I'd suggest a paladin for your friend and a druid for the healer. 
<br />

<br />
The paladin brings healing as well as tanking if needed. While the paladin is no warrior he tanks pretty well for 90% of situations outside of raiding. Even then there are times when a paladin is a better tank than a warrior in raid situations. He has ressurection spells which comes in great handy when you get in over your head and wipe. Although he gets these spells later than a cleric. The paladin also has excellent crowd control assist abilites with their stun line. Not only can this draw agro making it easier for an enchanter to survive crowd control, it also buys time for the enchanter to crowd control. A well played paladin is as good a friend to an enchanter as a well played cleric. Maybe more. Believe me, there are going to be times when you wish you had a melee class along. 
<br />

<br />
The druid would bring healing. Though their healing is not nearly as good as a cleric's it works fine in 80% of the situations. The biggest downside to a druid's healing is that he doesn't quite have the quick healing abilities of a paladin or cleric. Two boxing a druid I've done a lot of things that other encs have done two boxing a cleric. The added benefit is transport spells. You can pretty much port to within three zones of anywhere in EQ. SoW and SoE also help tons when you need to hike it if you get in trouble or are simply running through a zone. The druid is very good in the damage department as well with stackable dots and relatively quick casting nukes of different types.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
