                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pally, Druid, Enchanter very, very effective.
<br />

<br />
Ranger, Cleric, Enchanter is an option.
<br />

<br />
My personal experience when doing this unboxed.  Druids and Pallys adapt to the different tactics pet tanking requires faster and better than Rangers and Clerics.
<br />

<br />
I've had clerics try to heal my 20K hp pet with HoT - because that's what they are used to doing.  I've had more than one ranger become engrossed with doing as much dps with auto-archery to the point that re-snareing on charm breaks is an afterthought.
<br />

<br />
OTOH, druids are used to snareing everything in sight.  They are used to using the most mana efficient heal they can (because their direct heals suck).  The evac option (esp if they have fast exodus) and port capabilities make them very nice to have.  Pallys are used to using stun quickly to get agro.  The hardest thing about using a non-boxed pally in a pet tanking group is its extremely boring for them between charm breaks - especially if you are fighting non-casters.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Nokei Orhaste</a></span>
<br />
Coercer for <span style="color: blue"><a href="http://www.houseofaegis.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">House of Aegis</a></span>
<br />
Luclin
<br />
