                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Warrior - cleric - enchanter is my choice, these three can do pretty much anything that a full group can, and you can perform harder tasks with those. Just dont forget that any tanking class is very gear dependant.
<br />
While druid seems to be better choice, this aint true past level 60. You will face mobs that hit like trucks, and you may want best tanking along with best healing combined. Lack of snare is a major drawback, but it can be overcomed by cleric's quick stuns on ex-pet, and very fast/efficient heals on enchanter. Not very hard to charm with snare, but in a dungeon, or facing summoning/immune to snare mobs, cleric beats any druid hands down.
<br />
Also a big plus that you will always have group ready - just pick any of rest 12 classes, and you're set.
<br />

<br />
If you aim to reach 60+ levels quickly, go for enc-cle-war.
<br />
If you dont care how fast you level and dont play a whole lot, and 60+ game is not your nessesary aim. a druid + any other class would be better choice.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
