                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, as my 2 big characters are chanter and druid, I would LOVE to have them on seperate accounts.
<br />
I would go with a druid hands down over a cleric. Yeah, your heals are a bit rougher manawise. However as you get higher up, they really start strengtheming. Most of the situations you will be 3 boxing in, you wont need that much differential in healing. The biggie will be in the 30's, as all the druid will have is Greater Heal. But having been through that, you CAN chain cast GHeal enough to get through it. Also, snare weighs everyone. Plus, once you get into the 50's, the "skin" series may not have the HP and AC the cleric buffs have, but they DO have extra mana regen that STACKS with everything you got as a chanter. And let me tell you as a casual gamer, if I am getting hit a lot, I am doing something wrong. However, that extra mana is never a bad thing.
<br />
I too would hop on the chanter/druid/paly team.
<br />
Just my 2 coppers.. The main thing is have fun.. Don't like the feel of a group.. make a new one until you get the combo that works well for you. I have seen some ranja's or paly's do things that warriors couldn't because the person behind the toon enjoyed their class and it fit them well, so they were able to make the best of that class..
<br />
Good luck and welcome to Norrath  <img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=247107" target="_blank" class="postlink">Goloth</a>
