                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As I have and play an enchanter, cleric, druid, paladin, and sometimes a warrior I suppose I'll throw my 2 cents in.
<br />

<br />
I primarily play enchanter, as it sounds like you're going to do.  I find that, while druids are great to go with enchanters, a 2boxed druid isn't all that great.  Unless, of course, you happen to be able to charm/crowd control while kiting/pulling with druid at the same time.  I can multi-box fairly well, but even still I can only usually move one at a time effectively.  (Thats why casters are much easier to 2box than melee)
<br />

<br />
With a 2box, I find I can more effectively use the capabilities of a cleric vs those of a druid.  I have my /assist chanter and stun hotkey (very handy!), as well as hotkeys to heal each group member, etc.   A druid that does not stay mobile, however, doesn't come close to their capabilities.
<br />

<br />
Don't get me wrong, I love having druid partners, expecially when I'm charming.  Snare is great.... but you really need an independant druid to make it work as best as it can.  
<br />

<br />
Paladins are a solid choice, and are a decent compromise, but given the choice, I'd take a warrior for high-level fights, even just exp ones.
<br />

<br />
It really does depend on what you enjoy playing tho.  I'm not sure why your friend wanted to be a caster, tho.  If its to be more "independant", then you may want to consider shadowknight.  They are probably the most self-sufficient tank, having snare, invis, feign death, lifetaps, a pet (hah), etc.
<br />

<br />
If you are dead-set on a druid 2box tho, then paladin is a good choice, as sooner or later you will need a ressurection.  hehe.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tashim</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.botsguild.org/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brotherhood of the Spider</a>, <a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Rathe</a>
<br />

<br />
